00:42:04.790 --> 00:42:08.220
So I was I was quite
unhappy in a job that I had,

00:42:08.220 --> 00:42:09.680
but I thought that
I should carry

00:42:09.680 --> 00:42:11.360
on going because I
was helping people,

00:42:11.360 --> 00:42:13.040
even though I was
completely miserable.

00:42:13.040 --> 00:42:15.410
And that was what was
particularly unproductive

00:42:15.410 --> 00:42:16.130
about it.

00:42:16.130 --> 00:42:19.310
So I think that the way in
which you benefit yourself

00:42:19.310 --> 00:42:21.080
can be measured in many ways.

00:42:21.080 --> 00:42:23.960
And if you feel like
it's benefiting you,

00:42:23.960 --> 00:42:25.580
then it's not
necessarily martyrdom.

00:42:25.580 --> 00:42:27.020
If it feels like
it's hurting you

00:42:27.020 --> 00:42:29.090
and that it's making
your life miserable,

00:42:29.090 --> 00:42:31.220
then I think it
limits your ability

00:42:31.220 --> 00:42:32.699
to help people in the long run.

00:42:32.699 --> 00:42:35.240
So you help people tons for a
week, and then you're burnt out

00:42:35.240 --> 00:42:38.180
and you hate everybody, and then
you can't help anyone anymore.

00:42:38.180 --> 00:42:40.194
Or you help people a
bit less, and you also

00:42:40.194 --> 00:42:42.110
look after yourself or
do things for yourself,

00:42:42.110 --> 00:42:45.230
and then you have a
much longer run of being

00:42:45.230 --> 00:42:47.130
able to benefit other people.

00:42:47.130 --> 00:42:51.350
So that's some sort of vague
answer to that, I think.

